name: heme o synthase
classes: Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
reaction: (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + protoheme IX + H2O = diphosphate + ferroheme o [RN:R07411]
comment: The enzyme, found in many archaea, bacteria, and eukaryotes, produces heme o, which in many cases is further modified into heme a. In organisms that produce heme a, the enzyme forms a complex with heme a synthase.
